doubtful, uncertain, obscure. Ambiguity;
uncertainty of meaning.

Ambiguitas latens, a latent ambiguity;
ambiquitas patens, a patent ambiguity. See

AMI. A friend; as alien ami, an
alien belonging to a nation at peace with us;
prochein ami, a next friend suing or defending for an infant, married woman, etc.

ANNALY.

In Scotch law. To alienate;
to convey.

APPORT. L. Fr. In old English law.
Tax; tallage; tribute; imposition; payment;
charge; expenses. Kelham.

AQUATIC RIGHTS. Rights which individuals have to the use of the sea and rivers,
for the purpose of fishing and navigation,
and also to the soil in the sea and rivers.

AROMATARIUS. A word formerly used
for a grocer. 1 Vent. 142,


87 ARRAS

ARSENALS. Store-houses for arms;
dock-yards, magazines, and other military
stores.

ARTICULATELY. Article by article;
by distinct clauses or articles; by separate
propositions.

ASSISER. An assessor; juror; an officer
who has the care and oversight of weights
and measures. ;

ATTILA. In old English law.
tackle. Cowell.


Rigging;

AUMILDAR. In Indian law. Agent;
the holder of an office; an intendant and
collector of the revenue, uniting civil, military, and financial powers under the Mohammedan government.

AVOID. To annul; cancel; make void;
to destroy the efficacy of anything.


